LASSO Method of Linear Regression

In linear regression, find \(b_j\) in: \[ \hat{y}~=~b_0~+~b_1x_1~+~...~+~b_kx_k , \] that minimizes the value of \(\sum{(y-\hat{y})^2}\).

With LASSO regression we impose an additional constraint: \[\sum{| b_j |} \leq s .\]

A small \(s\) will make unimportant \(b_j\)'s go to zero.

Thus, we can analyze hundreds of variables without worrying about overfitting.
